4.67/5  rDev +3.8%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Now that the NEIPA style is finally it's own "official" style, I am happy to rate this beer today of all days!  It pours a perfectly cloudy and opaque deep yellow to orange with a frothy white head that stays on the surface and laces well.  It smells more of mango, guava, and papaya than I have ever smelled in a beer, with a faint hint of saison farmhouse like quality peeking through in the end.  Flavor is much the same, with a wine like and citric zest tying in unexpectedly yet beautifully with the tropical and ever so slightly tart compliments.  Feel is smooth and frothy, balanced with a touch of earthy dryness at the end, and completely masks the abv.  Overall, this is one amazing beer, and feel blessed to have tried.  Cheers, and thanks again Jay! 761 charactersLingenbrau, May 04, 2017
