4.32/5  rDev -4%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5The color of this monster of a beer is bright mango-orange, opaque, with a soft, level off-white foam that quickly recedes to a thin film and fuzzy collar.
Smell is absolutely, wonderfully complex yet pungent and almost funkily spiced, featuring notes of pineapple, mango, papaya, peach, pink peppercorn, a little onion, pine, peanut skin, and some spicy, ripe cedar.
Damn, this explodes on the tongue with sharp, tangy and spicy tropical and citrus notes, through a crisp, medium bodied ale that has a soft fizz and dry finish.
I taste mango, peach, pineapple, grapefruit, lemon, a little acidic green pine and green papaya, with Thai basil, musky cologne, and a far underlying cornbread biscuit.
On top of all this, it's 10%?!?! This is dangerous, as I detect no booze or alcohol whatsoever, and it comes on quick because there are so many other things going on to take your mind off of the strength of what you're actually drinking.
The Streets is absolutely bombastic, maybe too much so, but simultaneously it is much more enjoyable than some of the other “hop overload” DIPAs or TIPAs certain big name NE-style IPA breweries put out once or twice per year to great fanfare. 1,187 charactersSabtos, Mar 30, 2017
