4.67/5  rDev +3.8%look: 3.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75A: Flat, golden glossy pour. Was expecting a milkshake like Headroom/Haze...not a bad thing by any means, just surprising. Honestly looks closer to the beers Trillium was releasing when Canton first opened and they were still dialing their shit in. Slight white foamy head that dissapeared quite quickly. Minimal effervescence. Not the most inviting beer I've poured. But what the fuck do looks matter anyway. 
S: Super rich, tropical dankness. Pineapple and peaches. Boozy...rindy 
T: Whoa now. Clementines. Orange rind. Booze. Lots of fucking booze. Like a boozy orange julius. as it warms there is a very prominent vodka taste to me, but I honestly like it. Slight hop/yeast burn on the finish. Quaffable. a 10% quaffable beer. Dangerous. flavors keep evolving...
Honestly it's like a smorgasbord of flavors.  I almost feel like I need bullet points for this beer as it warms up
First sips: clementines, rind
Middle first: Exotic, tropical, bitter
Middle finish: Boozy, sticky, sweetness. dank.
Finish: Dry, vinuous, dry white wine. sticky sticky sticky dryness that clings to the roof of my mouth. 
F: Oily, sticky, very full bodied. Tastes a lot thicker than it looks. If I drank this from a can I would assume it was full of hop and yeast particulate.(sometimes when I describe characteristics of NE ipa's it sounds negative, but they are not meant to be. give me those milkshakes)
O: Look, this is a 10% ipa. If you want something that doesn't taste like alcohol I would try a beer that isn't almost flammable. Really interesting and fun beer to drink, one at a time! You can definitely pick out subtleties of all the different hops that were added. I would highly recommend sipping on this, high abv aside. I drank this for about an hour, and by the end it was like a totally different beer. Really cool stuff. That said, there is definitely a yeasty/hop burn that will hopefully disappear in a week or so. Look forward to trying again!
As always, Trillium knocks it out of the park with the anniversary beer. Enjoying this more than Headroom from this past august. 2,080 charactersJonnyJuicebox, Mar 20, 2017
