Pours cloudy gold with an orangy hue. Typical short-lived head and minimal lacing for a Trillium hoppy offering. Aromatics are pungently hoppy with loads of candied fruit. Pineapple, mango, peach, grapefruit, and bubblegum. Medium bodied with a slick, somewhat oily mouthfeel. Sugar-dusted tropical fruit on the palate with a stinging hop presence and an undercurrent of boozy alcohol. A glancing blow of bitterness follows through along with some lingering honey sweetness. Finishes with boozy fruit and a crack of the resin whip. 
This beer is huge and hoppy but has low carbonation (lower than usual for a Trillium) and the mouthfeel suffers. A bit on the sweeter side as I've come to expect a drier character from Trillium, but an excellent example of a IIIPA. 797 charactersbrewandbbq, Mar 20, 2017
