4.28/5  rDev -4.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Appearance: Beautiful hazy orange, almost iridescent in light
Aroma: Holy grapefruit and amarillo/mosaic batman. Smells like a box of citrus and mangoes from Florida.
Taste: No funk from Columbus which is a plus or minus depending on personal preference, traditionally their bittering hop. At first got tons of amarillo/mosaic, but as it warms the complexity of all the specialty hop flavors really comes out.  Really recommend taking your time with this one, especially at 10% abv.  Upon warming you get the white wine from nelson, and this crazy key lime and lemon thing from the galaxy, simcoe and el dorado.  You get a lot of the candied peach and cherry on the back end from it at the bottom of the glass from el dorado and the yeast esters.
Mouthfeel: A bit thinner and dried out for trillium but that happens with a 10% pale beer. More carbonated and fizzy feeling than usual, not sure if its the water or what, because the head is minimal. Slick hop oily finish is always welcome, sticky feeling that coats your mouth on the finish but not under attenuated, you definitely get some heat from the booze.
Overall: First Impression was that they combined the specialty hops from all of their street beers and made it 10%...which is exactly what it is.  For such a high alcohol percentage it lacks balance, but it is really fun to drink and try to pick out each hop flavor.  It lacks a bit of dank bitterness for me personally and tastes like a massive dry hop.  As it warms up you can really pick out a lot of specialty hop flavors, so its a great one-off for a celebratory beer.  It's like a "cleaning out the hop refrigerator" beer that a home-brewer would make so it's definitely special and something worth getting your hands on.  LET THIS SIT and enjoy, buzzed after the first one and the second is probably too many. 1,830 charactersafro_ginja, Mar 19, 2017
